The paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for generating digital art, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The focus is on digital image transition, which involves manipulating images, and this can be related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of mutation operators and evolutionary mechanisms suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) approach. The production of generative art involves multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning techniques (cs.LG).
